ce:section.ce:para:
To avoid the reduction of DOX activity by light, the experiments and the storage of drug-loaded NPs were conducted in the dark. The drying method was lyophilization. The specific drug loading process was as follows. CoFe2O4&SiO2-CTAB obtained in Section 2.2.3 was dispersed into 50 mL of acetone and refluxed at 70 ℃ for 48 h. Old acetone was replaced by fresh one and refluxtion was continued for another 48 h. It was washed three times sequentially with ethanol and ultrapure water. After magnetic separation, the solid was CoFe2O4&mSiO2. The above CoFe2O4&mSiO2 NPs were redispersed in 10 mL of ultrapure water. 10 mg DOX (m

                              DOX
                           ) was added and stirred at 25 ℃ for 48 h in dark. Magnetic separation was carried out and the solid was washed with ultrapure water to remove DOX adsorbed on the surface of the NPs. The supernatant was combined and the total volume was measured. The absorbance of the supernatant at 485 nm was measured using a UV-Vis spectrophotometer. The mass of unloaded DOX (m

                              unloaded
                           ) was further calculated. The solid obtained was the DOX-CoFe2O4&mSiO2. Then CDs were grafted on the DOX-CoFe2O4&mSiO2 to give DOX-CoFe2O4&mSiO2/CDs by the same method described above (Section 2.2.4). DOX-CoFe2O4&mSiO2/CDs NPs were freeze-dried and their mass (m

                              total
                           ) were weighed.
